+1. EXECUTIVE SNAPSHOT (FACTUAL)
+
+1.1. What KNEZ Is Today (Code-Verified)
+
+1.1.1. KNEZ as Implemented in knez/knez_core/app.py
+- KNEZ is a FastAPI application defined in [app.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/app.py).
+- The application is created by the function `create_app()` and exported as `app`.
+- The app assembles multiple subsystems via routers:
+  - Core chat completion API: `knez.knez_core.api.completions.router`
+  - Health API: `knez.knez_core.api.health.router`
+  - Session resume/fork API: `knez.knez_core.api.sessions.router`
+  - Event tailing API: `knez.knez_core.events.api.router`
+  - Replay API: `knez.knez_core.replay.api.router`
+  - Memory inspection API: `knez.knez_core.memory.api.router`
+  - TAQWIN integration API: `knez.integrations.taqwin.adapter.router`
+  - Cognitive layer API: `knez.cognitive.api.router`
+- The app also creates and stores a `Router` instance on `app.state.router`, constructed with:
+  - Three `CloudBackend` instances, configured via environment variables:
+    - `KNEZ_CLOUD_A_URL` (default `http://localhost:8001`)
+    - `KNEZ_CLOUD_B_URL` (default `http://localhost:8002`)
+    - `KNEZ_CLOUD_C_URL` (default `http://localhost:8003`)
+  - One `LocalBackend` instance (default model and endpoint defined in `knez.knez_core.models.local_backend.LocalBackend`).
+- On startup, the app starts an `EventStore` via `knez.knez_core.events.store.get_store().start()`.
+- On shutdown, it stops the `EventStore` via `get_store().stop()`.
+
+1.1.2. Server Entrypoint in run.py
+- The executable entrypoint for KNEZ is [run.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/run.py).
+- The `main()` function:
+  - Reads `KNEZ_HOST` (default `"0.0.0.0"`) and `KNEZ_PORT` (default `"8000"`).
+  - Runs `uvicorn.run(app, host=host, port=port, log_level="info")` using the KNEZ FastAPI `app`.
+- When `run.py` is invoked as `__main__`, `main()` is executed.
+
+1.1.3. External TAQWIN Server
+- A separate FastAPI application exists in [taqwin/server.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/taqwin/server.py).
+- This TAQWIN server:
+  - Instantiates a FastAPI `app`.
+  - Includes the TAQWIN router from [taqwin/handler.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/taqwin/handler.py).
+  - Runs via `uvicorn.run` using environment variables:
+    - `TAQWIN_HOST` (default `"0.0.0.0"`)
+    - `TAQWIN_PORT` (default `"9001"`).
+- TAQWIN is an external service that calls KNEZ through HTTP (see `taqwin.knez_client`).
+
+1.1.4. OpenAI-Compatible Compatibility Layer
+- A separate FastAPI app for IDE compatibility is defined in [knez/compat/app.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/compat/app.py).
+- It creates a FastAPI app named "KNEZ Compat" and includes the router from [knez/compat/api.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/compat/api.py).
+- The compatibility layer implements:
+  - `POST /v1/chat/completions` (OpenAI-style, streaming and non-streaming).
+  - `POST /v1/responses` (OpenAI Responses API).
+  - `GET /v1/models` (model listing with capability flags).
+- The compat endpoints proxy into the core KNEZ app (`knez.knez_core.app.app`) using `httpx.AsyncClient(app=core_app, base_url="http://core")`.
+
+1.1.5. Data Files
+- The `data/` directory (see [data](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/data)) contains:
+  - `events.log`: event store log file used by `knez.knez_core.events.store.EventStore`.
+  - `memory.db`: SQLite database used by `knez.knez_core.memory.store.MemoryStore`.
+  - `sessions.db`: SQLite database used by `knez.knez_core.sessions.store` for:
+    - `session_lineage` table.
+    - `failover_events` table.
+    - `snapshot_deltas` table.
+    - `resume_snapshots` table.
+    - `memory_candidates` table.
+
+1.1.6. Tests as Behavioral Specification
+- The `tests/` directory contains pytest-based tests that exercise:
+  - Cognitive layer behavior (see [tests/test_cognitive_layer.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_cognitive_layer.py)).
+  - Memory governance and reflection (see [tests/test_memory_governance.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_memory_governance.py)).
+  - Memory extraction and replay (see [tests/test_memory.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_memory.py)).
+  - Replay engine and session outcome computation (see [tests/test_replay.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_replay.py)).
+  - Failover, local failover, and gap policy (see [tests/test_failover_loop.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_failover_loop.py), [tests/test_local_failover.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_local_failover.py), [tests/test_gap_policy.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_gap_policy.py)).
+  - Continuous and stress sessions (see [tests/test_continuous_sessions.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_continuous_sessions.py), [tests/test_stress_sessions.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_stress_sessions.py)).
+  - Influence execution and interface (see [tests/test_influence_execution.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_influence_execution.py), [tests/test_influence_interface.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_influence_interface.py)).
+  - Shadow influence (see [tests/test_shadow_influence.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_shadow_influence.py)).
+  - TAQWIN adapter events (see [tests/test_taqwin_adapter.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_taqwin_adapter.py)).
+  - Tokenizer consistency and TTFT safeguards (see [tests/test_tokenizer_consistency.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_tokenizer_consistency.py), [tests/test_ttft_keepalive.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_ttft_keepalive.py)).
+
+1.2. What KNEZ Is Not (Based on Code Only)
+
+1.2.1. No Autonomous Agent Execution Loop
+- There is no code that continuously generates tasks or prompts without external HTTP requests.
+- The core generation entrypoint is `chat_completions` in [knez_core/api/completions.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/api/completions.py), which only runs when invoked via HTTP.
+- There is no scheduler or background task that asks LLMs to act without a client-initiated request.
+
+1.2.2. No Tool Execution Engine
+- No module in the repository implements generic tool execution, shell command invocation, or external API orchestration based on LLM decisions.
+- The only â€śtoolsâ€ť present are integration adapters: TAQWIN integration in [knez/integrations/taqwin](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/integrations/taqwin) and the external TAQWIN server in [taqwin](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/taqwin).
+- The compatibility layer accepts OpenAI-style `tools` fields but does not execute them; it emits `tool_ignored` events and strips them before forwarding.
+
+1.2.3. No General-Purpose Autonomous Workflow Engine
+- There is no code that chains multiple sessions or tasks autonomously.
+- Session forking and resume logic in [knez_core/api/sessions.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/api/sessions.py) are driven by explicit API calls, not automatic background processes.
+- Cognitive layer components (dashboard, governance, runbook, shadow, approval) compute metrics and insights but do not directly modify router configuration or call back into generation endpoints in a loop.
+
+1.2.4. No Frontend or User Interface in This Repository
+- There is no Next.js or web dashboard implementation present in the repository.
+- The only user-facing surface implemented here is the FastAPI HTTP APIs and the TAQWIN server.
+- All mentions of dashboards or frontends in [prd.txt](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/prd.txt) are design-level descriptions, not implemented code.
+
+1.2.5. No Explicit Authentication or Authorization Layer
+- There is no authentication middleware or token validation implemented in the KNEZ FastAPI app.
+- The FastAPI `app` is created without dependencies that enforce API keys or OAuth.
+- Any security or auth behavior would have to be implemented externally; it is not present in this codebase.
+
+1.3. Problem KNEZ Solves Right Now (From Code)
+
+1.3.1. Multi-Backend Chat Completion Routing
+- KNEZ orchestrates chat completion requests across multiple backends:
+  - `CloudBackend` instances (see [knez_core/models/cloud_backend.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/models/cloud_backend.py)).
+  - A `LocalBackend` (see [knez_core/models/local_backend.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/models/local_backend.py)).
+- Routing decisions are made by `Router` in [knez_core/router/router.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/router/router.py) using:
+  - Classifier-based model selection (`knez_core/router/classifier.py`).
+  - Health-based scoring (`knez_core/router/scorer.py`).
+  - Influence from memory hints and cognitive influence contracts (`knez_core/memory/consumption/hint_generator.py` and `knez/cognitive/influence/contracts.py`).
+- Requests flow through `chat_completions` which:
+  - Creates a `GenerationRequest`.
+  - Either streams tokens or returns a full response depending on `stream` flag.
+
+1.3.2. Continuous Checkpointing and SQLite Persistence
+- During streaming, the core `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint:
+  - Uses a `CheckpointWorker` (inner class in `knez_core/api/completions.py`) for the streaming endpoint.
+  - Uses `RedisStream` ([knez_core/checkpoints/redis_stream.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/checkpoints/redis_stream.py)) to temporarily buffer token checkpoints.
+  - Uses `SQLiteWriter` ([knez_core/checkpoints/sqlite_writer.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/checkpoints/sqlite_writer.py)) to persist token checkpoints into SQLite.
+- For failover and continuation, `knez_core/checkpoints/reader.py` implements a `CheckpointWorker` that:
+  - Reads from Redis.
+  - Flushes token buffers into `sessions.db`.
+  - Associates metadata with checkpoints.
+
+1.3.3. Failover and Continuation
+- The `FailoverManager` in [knez_core/failover/manager.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/failover/manager.py):
+  - Reads checkpoints via `checkpoints.reader`.
+  - Builds continuation prompts via `failover.continuation.build_continuation_prompt`.
+  - Uses `LocalBackend` to simulate local failover.
+  - Logs failover events via `sessions.store.log_failover`.
+  - Emits telemetry metrics via `telemetry.metrics.Metrics`.
+- The failover logic is exercised in tests:
+  - [tests/test_failover_loop.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_failover_loop.py).
+  - [tests/test_local_failover.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/tests/test_local_failover.py).
+
+1.3.4. Session Lineage and Resume Snapshots
+- `knez_core/sessions/store.py` implements:
+  - Session lineage recording: `record_session_lineage`.
+  - Resume snapshot compilation: `compile_resume_snapshot_for_session`.
+  - Snapshot delta recording: `record_snapshot_delta`.
+  - Storage of resume snapshots and deltas in `sessions.db`.
+- `knez_core/api/sessions.py` exposes:
+  - `POST /sessions/{session_id}/resume`: create a new session with a compiled snapshot from an existing session.
+  - `GET /sessions/{session_id}/resume_snapshot`: retrieve the compiled snapshot for inspection.
+  - `POST /sessions/{session_id}/fork`: create a forked session lineage record.
+
+1.3.5. Memory Extraction and Storage
+- `knez_core/memory/gate.py`:
+  - Replays session events via `replay_session`.
+  - Uses `summary_to_dict` and `Insight` from replay models.
+  - Constructs `MemoryCandidate` objects using `new_memory_candidate`.
+  - Writes durable memory entries via `MemoryStore`.
+- `knez_core/memory/store.py` persists memory into `data/memory.db` SQLite database.
+- `knez_core/memory/api.py` exposes:
+  - `GET /memory`: list memory items with filters.
+  - `GET /memory/{memory_id}`: fetch a single memory item.
+
+1.3.6. Replay and Reflection over Event Logs
+- `knez_core/replay/engine.py`:
+  - Loads events from the `EventStore`.
+  - Builds a `SessionReplay` with phases and stats.
+  - Generates insights via `replay.insights`.
+  - Builds a summary via `replay.summary`.
+  - Emits reflection events via `replay.reflection.emit_reflection_events`.
+- `knez_core/replay/api.py` exposes:
+  - `GET /sessions/{session_id}/replay`: returns replay details.
+  - `GET /sessions/{session_id}/summary`: returns summary as dict.
+  - `GET /sessions/{session_id}/insights`: returns high-level insights.
+
+1.3.7. Cognitive Layer Analysis and Governance
+- The cognitive layer in `knez/cognitive` provides:
+  - Runbook generation: `knez.cognitive.runbook.generate_runbook`.
+  - Dashboard state aggregation: `knez.cognitive.dashboard.get_state_overview` and related functions.
+  - Governance evaluation and influence readiness evaluation: `knez.cognitive.governance.GovernanceEvaluator` and `IRIEvaluator`.
+  - Shadow influence simulation: `knez.cognitive.shadow.simulator.ShadowSimulator`.
+  - Approval gate: `knez.cognitive.approval.api.ApprovalService`.
+- These components consume events and replayed data to derive metrics and governance records.
+
+1.3.8. TAQWIN Integration
+- KNEZ integrates with an external TAQWIN analysis and recommendation engine:
+  - `knez.integrations.taqwin.adapter` exposes `/taqwin/events` inside the KNEZ app.
+  - TAQWIN payloads are validated and converted into KNEZ events.
+  - The external TAQWIN server uses `taqwin.knez_client` to call KNEZ `/v1/chat/completions` and `/taqwin/events`.
+
+1.3.9. IDE Compatibility
+- KNEZ exposes an OpenAI-compatible surface via `knez/compat/api.py`:
+  - Normalizes SSE behavior to `data:` frames plus `[DONE]`.
+  - Normalizes error payloads into `{ "error": { "message": ..., "type": ... } }`.
+  - Provides `POST /v1/responses` for clients that expect the OpenAI Responses API.
+  - Exposes `GET /v1/models` with capability flags.
+
+1.4. Deployment and Runtime Assumptions (From Code)
+
+1.4.1. Environment Variables for KNEZ Core
+- `KNEZ_HOST` and `KNEZ_PORT` control the FastAPI server interface (see [run.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/run.py)).
+- `KNEZ_CLOUD_A_URL`, `KNEZ_CLOUD_B_URL`, `KNEZ_CLOUD_C_URL` define remote model endpoints.
+
+1.4.2. Environment and Paths for Storage
+- `knez_core.events.store.EventStore` defaults to `data/events.log` and ensures the `data` directory exists.
+- `knez_core.sessions.store._conn()` uses a fixed path `data/sessions.db` and ensures `data` exists.
+- `knez_core.memory.store.MemoryStore` uses `data/memory.db` and ensures the containing directory exists.
+
+1.4.3. TAQWIN Runtime Environment
+- `TAQWIN_HOST` and `TAQWIN_PORT` control the TAQWIN server (see [taqwin/server.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/taqwin/server.py)).
+- `KNEZ_BASE_URL` in `taqwin.knez_client` controls how TAQWIN reaches KNEZ (default `http://localhost:8000`).
+
+1.4.4. Metrics Export
+- `knez_core.telemetry.metrics` uses Prometheus `Counter` and `Gauge` from `prometheus_client`.
+- No explicit HTTP endpoint for Prometheus metrics is defined in this repository; exporting metrics requires Prometheusâ€™ instrumentation defaults or an external server configuration, which is not present in this code.
+
+1.4.5. Not Determinable from Code
+- There is no code that configures reverse tunnels, Kubernetes, or cloud deployment environments.
+- High-level operational details (Kaggle, Colab, Paperspace) appear only in [prd.txt](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/prd.txt) and not in executable code.
+- Scaling characteristics (number of workers, process models) are not defined in code and would depend on how `uvicorn` is invoked externally.
