+3. SYSTEM PHASE CLASSIFICATION
+
+3.1. Phase Definitions (For This Audit)
+- Conversational System: ability to accept conversational inputs and produce responses, with streaming and session IDs.
+- Memory System: ability to derive, store, and retrieve durable memories from past interactions.
+- Reflection / Judgment System: ability to analyze past events, compute insights, and classify them with governance rules.
+- Assisted Automation System: ability to automate side processes (e.g., failover, continuation) triggered by system events.
+- Autonomous System: ability to initiate new tasks or behaviors without direct external requests.
+
+3.2. Conversational System
+
+3.2.1. Status
+- Marked as: IMPLEMENTED.
