+4. CORE REQUEST FLOW (END-TO-END)
+
+4.1. /v1/chat/completions (Core KNEZ)
+
+4.1.1. Entry and Request Model
+- Implemented in [knez_core/api/completions.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/api/completions.py).
+- Request type: `ChatCompletionRequest`:
+  - `model: Optional[str]`
+  - `messages: list[ChatMessage]`
+  - `stream: bool = True`
+  - `temperature: Optional[float]`
+  - `max_tokens: Optional[int]`
+  - `top_p: Optional[float]`
+  - `session_id: Optional[str]`
+
+4.1.2. Session ID and Lineage
+- If `session_id` is not provided:
+  - A new `session_id` is generated using `uuid.uuid4().hex`.
+- `get_session_lineage(session_id)` is called:
+  - If it returns `None`, `record_session_lineage` is invoked with:
+    - `parent_session_id=None`.
+    - `resume_snapshot_id=None`.
+    - `resume_mode="fresh"`.
+    - `resume_reason=None`.
+- This writes a row in `session_lineage` table and emits a `session_created` event.
+
+4.1.3. Event Emission: Session Start
+- An event is emitted using `get_emitter().emit(...)`:
+  - `event_type=EventType.INPUT`.
+  - `event_name="session_start"`.
+  - `source=EventSource.KNEZ_CORE`.
+  - `severity=EventSeverity.INFO`.
+  - Payload includes:
+    - `model`.
+    - `stream` flag.
+    - `message_count`.
+- The `EventStore` eventually flushes this event to `data/events.log`.
+
+4.1.4. GenerationRequest Construction
+- A `GenerationRequest` is instantiated with:
+  - `messages=req.messages`.
+  - `temperature=req.temperature or 0.7`.
+  - `max_tokens=req.max_tokens`.
+  - `top_p=req.top_p or 1.0`.
+  - `stream=req.stream`.
+  - `metadata={"model": req.model or "", "session_id": session_id}`.
+
+4.1.5. Streaming Path
+- If `req.stream` is `True`:
+  - `_sse_stream(request, gen_request, session_id)` is used as the generator for `StreamingResponse` with `media_type="text/event-stream"`.
+- Within `_sse_stream`:
+  - A `CheckpointWorker` is instantiated with `session_id`.
+  - A router object is retrieved: `router_obj: Router = request.app.state.router`.
+  - A backend is chosen:
+    - It first tries to select a `LocalBackend` instance from `router_obj.backends`.
+    - If no `LocalBackend` is found, `router_obj.select(gen_request)` is awaited.
+  - As tokens are generated:
+    - The function implements a time-to-first-token safeguard:
+      - If no token is produced within a timeout (5 seconds), it emits a keep-alive SSE message `{"id": session_id, "object": "keep-alive"}` and increments a metrics counter via `Metrics().inc_ttft_safeguard(backend.model_id)`.
+    - For each token:
+      - If the HTTP request is disconnected, the loop breaks.
+      - Tokens equal to `"__DONE__"` trigger token stream end events.
+      - Other tokens:
+        - Are submitted to the `CheckpointWorker` with token index and string.
+        - Are yielded as SSE data frames (e.g., `data: {"id": session_id, "object": "chat.completion.chunk", ...}\n\n`).
+  - `CheckpointWorker`:
+    - Submits tokens to an in-memory queue.
+    - Periodically flushes to Redis and SQLite based on interval and token count.
+    - Emits checkpoint events when flushes happen.
+
+4.1.6. Non-Streaming Path
+- If `req.stream` is `False`:
+  - `router_obj: Router = request.app.state.router` is obtained.
+  - A `LocalBackend` is searched in `router_obj.backends`.
+    - If found, it is used; otherwise, `router_obj.select(gen_request)` is called.
+  - A list `collected: list[str]` accumulates tokens from `backend.generate`.
+  - `BackendFailure` exceptions:
+    - If raised, a JSON error body `{"error": "backend_stream_interrupted", "reason": <str(e)>}` is returned as a `StreamingResponse` with `application/json`.
+  - On success:
+    - The tokens in `collected` are concatenated into a single string.
+    - The final response is:
+      - `{"id": session_id, "object": "chat.completion", "choices": [{"message": {"role": "assistant", "content": "<text>"}, "finish_reason": "stop"}]}`.
+    - This is returned as a `StreamingResponse` with `media_type="application/json"` (non-streaming HTTP response).
