+4.2. /v1/chat/completions (Compat Layer)
+
+4.2.1. Entry and Request Model
+- Implemented in [knez/compat/api.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/compat/api.py).
+- Request type: `ChatCompletionsRequest`:
+  - Mirrors OpenAI fields:
+    - `model`, `messages`, `stream`, `temperature`, `max_tokens`, `top_p`, `session_id`.
+    - Additional `tools` and `tool_choice` for passive tool compatibility.
+
+4.2.2. Tool Handling and Events
+- If `tools` or `tool_choice` is present:
+  - `_emit_tool_ignored(session_id, "chat.completions", tools, tool_choice)` is called.
+  - This uses `get_emitter()` and emits:
+    - `event_type=EventType.ACTION`.
+    - `event_name="tool_ignored"`.
+    - `source=EventSource.TOOL`.
+    - `severity=EventSeverity.INFO`.
+    - Payload includes:
+      - `request_type`.
+      - `tools_present`.
+      - `tool_choice_present`.
+- The actual request forwarded to core excludes `tools` and `tool_choice`.
+
+4.2.3. SSE Normalization and Keep-Alive Control
+- A helper `_normalize_sse_stream(upstream, keepalive_enabled)`:
+  - Consumes SSE frames from the upstream core app.
+  - Splits by `\n\n` into frames.
+  - Processes lines starting with `data: `.
+  - For `[DONE]`:
+    - Emits `data: [DONE]\n\n` and returns.
+  - For JSON payloads:
+    - If `object == "keep-alive"`:
+      - If `keepalive_enabled` is `True`, forwards the frame unchanged; otherwise, suppresses it.
+    - If an `error` field exists without `choices`:
+      - Normalizes to `{"error": {"message": <message>, "type": <type>}}`.
+    - Otherwise:
+      - Forwards the JSON object.
+  - For non-JSON payloads:
+    - Forwards as `data: <payload>\n\n`.
+- `keepalive_enabled` is determined by:
+  - `KNEZ_SSE_KEEPALIVE` environment variable (lowercased).
+  - If equal to `"false"`, keep-alive frames are suppressed.
+
+4.2.4. Streaming and Non-Streaming Proxy
+- For streaming requests:
+  - A `StreamingResponse` is returned with `media_type="text/event-stream"`.
+  - Uses `httpx.AsyncClient(app=core_app, base_url="http://core")` to call core `/v1/chat/completions` in streaming mode.
+- For non-streaming requests:
+  - Forwarded via `client.post` to core.
+  - Response:
+    - On JSON parse failure:
+      - Returns `{"error": {"message": "invalid_upstream_response", "type": "backend_error"}}` with upstream status code.
+    - On JSON with `error` but no `choices`:
+      - Normalizes the error as above and returns with upstream status code.
+    - Otherwise:
+      - Forwards the JSON and status code unchanged.
