+5. ROUTING & MODEL EXECUTION
+
+5.1. Router Selection Logic
+
+5.1.1. Router Construction
+- `Router` is instantiated in `knez_core/app.py`:
+  - Backends: three `CloudBackend`s and one `LocalBackend`.
+  - `Router` receives this list and sets up its internal structures.
+
+5.1.2. Router.select Flow
+- Defined in [knez_core/router/router.py](file:///c:/Users/syedm/Downloads/ASSETS/KNEZ/knez/knez_core/router/router.py).
+- High-level steps:
+  - Classify the request using `classifier.classify(gen_request)`.
+  - Score backends using `scorer.score_health(backends, metrics)`.
+  - Generate memory hints via `MemoryHintGenerator`.
+  - Apply `RoutingInfluenceAdapter` to adjust scores based on stable influence signals and runtime switches.
+  - Select a backend based on scores and influence.
+  - Emit routing decision event and memory hint usage events.
+
+5.2. Backend Scoring and Health
+
+5.2.1. CloudBackend
+- Implemented in `knez_core/models/cloud_backend.py`.
+- Uses HTTP requests to remote model APIs using `httpx.AsyncClient`.
+- Provides `health()` method returning `BackendHealth` with status, latency, and other metrics.
+- Uses `Metrics` to record latency, failures, and tokens/sec.
+
+5.2.2. LocalBackend
+- Implemented in `knez_core/models/local_backend.py`.
+- Sends HTTP POST requests to `/api/generate` endpoint of a local model runtime.
+- Streams newline-delimited JSON lines.
+- For each JSON object:
+  - Checks `done` flag to mark completion.
+  - Yields tokens and calls `stream_callback` accordingly.
+- Emits events:
+  - `EventType.ANALYSIS` and `EventType.ACTION` events for token streaming and backend failures.
+- Uses `Metrics` for tokens/sec and latency metrics.
+
+5.3. Influence Hooks
+
+5.3.1. RoutingInfluenceAdapter
+- Implemented in `knez.cognitive.influence.contracts`.
+- Provides:
+  - `apply(session_id, scored_backends)` â†’ returns:
+    - Possibly adjusted score/backends.
+    - `RoutingInfluenceTrace` describing adjustments.
+- Influence data is derived from:
+  - Governance decisions (InfluenceReadinessRecord).
+  - Runtime switches (e.g., enabling/disabling influence for routing).
+
+5.3.2. What Influence Hooks Do NOT Do
+- They do not directly persist changes to router configuration to disk.
+- They do not create new sessions or tasks.
+- They operate strictly within the context of a single routing decision.
+
+5.4. Treatment of Model Strings
+
+5.4.1. Model Field Handling
+- `ChatCompletionRequest.model` is optional and used in `GenerationRequest.metadata["model"]`.
+- The routerâ€™s backend selection does not directly inspect this string for selection logic in the provided code; classification and scoring rely more on request features and health metrics.
+- Exact matching or mapping of model IDs to backends is not determinable from code beyond:
+  - `CloudBackend` uses `model_id` fields set at construction.
+  - `LocalBackend` has a `model_id` default parameter.
