+9. EVENT SYSTEM (TRUTH SOURCE)
+
+9.1. Event Schema
+
+9.1.1. Event Types
+- Defined in `knez_core/events/schema.py`:
+  - `EventType.INPUT`.
+  - `EventType.ANALYSIS`.
+  - `EventType.DECISION`.
+  - `EventType.ACTION`.
+  - `EventType.REFLECTION`.
+  - `EventType.PERSISTENCE`.
+  - `EventType.ERROR`.
+
+9.1.2. EventSeverity
+- `DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARN`, `ERROR`.
+
+9.1.3. EventSource
+- `knez_core`, `llfs`, `model`, `taqwin`, `tool`, `system`.
+
+9.1.4. Event Dataclass
+- Each event includes:
+  - `event_id`.
+  - `timestamp` (ISO string).
+  - `session_id`.
+  - `task_id`.
+  - `event_type`.
+  - `event_name`.
+  - `source`.
+  - `severity`.
+  - `payload` (dict).
+  - `tags` (list of strings).
+
+9.2. Emission Points
+
+9.2.1. Core API
+- `chat_completions` emits:
+  - `session_start`, `token_stream`, `token_stream_end`, and failure events.
+- `sessions.store` emits:
+  - `session_created`, `session_resumed`, `session_forked`, `resume_snapshot_compiled`, `resume_snapshot_loaded`, `snapshot_delta_recorded`.
+- `events` modules and memory gate emit various events for checkpointing and memory.
+
+9.2.2. Cognitive Layer
+- `governance` emits reflection events about memory and influence readiness.
+- `dashboard` reads but does not emit.
+- `shadow` emits delta-related events via its store (where implemented).
+
+9.2.3. TAQWIN Integration
+- `knez/integrations/taqwin/events.py`:
+  - Emits `taqwin_input_received`, `taqwin_analysis_completed`, `taqwin_proposal_observed`, `taqwin_payload_rejected`.
+
+9.3. Storage Guarantees
+
+9.3.1. EventStore
+- `knez_core/events/store.py`:
+  - Maintains an in-memory queue.
+  - Writes events line-by-line as JSON to `data/events.log`.
+  - `start()` begins a background task to flush events.
+  - `stop()` stops the background task.
+
+9.3.2. Tail Operations
+- `EventStore.tail(limit, event_type, session_id, task_id)`:
+  - Returns the last `limit` events matching provided filters by scanning the log file.
+
+9.4. Replay Semantics
+
+9.4.1. Replay Pipeline
+- `replay/engine.replay_session`:
+  - Loads events for a session via `get_store().tail` or other store methods.
+  - Computes:
+    - Phases via `build_timeline_phases`.
+    - Stats via `compute_stats`.
+    - Insights via `generate_insights`.
+    - Summary via `build_session_summary`.
+  - Emits reflection events via `emit_reflection_events`.
+
+9.5. Coupling to Cognitive Layer
+
+9.5.1. Event-Driven Cognitive Computations
+- Cognitive modules consume events via:
+  - `EventStore` from `knez_core.events.store`.
+  - Replay results from `knez_core.replay.engine`.
+  - Reflection events produced by replay and governance.
+
+9.5.2. No Direct Hard Coupling into Router
+- Influence decisions are computed by `governance` and `IRIEvaluator`.
+- They are only applied to routing via the influence adapter and runtime switches, which must be enabled.
+- There is no code that permanently rewrites router configuration based on cognitive results.
+
+10. COGNITIVE LAYER REALITY CHECK
+
+10.1. Dashboard
+
+10.1.1. What It Computes
+- `knez/cognitive/dashboard.py`:
+  - Aggregates event-based metrics including:
+    - Governance insights counts.
+    - Influence readiness distributions.
+    - Stability and drift metrics.
+    - TAQWIN session observations.
+
+10.1.2. Inputs
+- Event logs via `EventStore`.
+- Reflection events from governance and replay.
+
+10.1.3. Effect on Execution
+- Does not affect routing, failover, or generation.
+- Observational only.
+
+10.2. Audit
+
+10.2.1. What It Computes
+- `knez/cognitive/audit.py` defines functions such as:
+  - `audit_influence_readiness_consistency`.
+  - `audit_shadow_vs_live_divergence`.
+  - `audit_drift_monitor_vs_switches`.
+- These compute high-level checks and statuses based on reflection and influence state.
+
+10.2.2. Inputs
+- Reflection events.
+- Influence readiness records.
+- Shadow simulation summaries.
+
+10.2.3. Effect on Execution
+- Produces structured reports for inspection.
+- No direct effect on Router or backend selection.
+
+10.3. Runbook
+
+10.3.1. What It Computes
+- `knez/cognitive/runbook.generate_runbook(session_id)`:
+  - Produces a structured textual runbook for a session, including:
+    - Timeline of key events.
+    - TAQWIN interactions.
+    - Routing decisions, checkpoint events, and stability observations.
+
+10.3.2. Inputs
+- `replay_session(session_id)` results.
+- `summary_to_dict` results.
+- TAQWIN-related events mapped via `_TAQWIN_EVENT_PREFIXES`.
+
+10.3.3. Effect on Execution
+- Observational; does not change any runtime behavior.
+
+10.4. Shadow Influence
+
+10.4.1. What It Computes
+- `knez/cognitive/shadow/simulator.ShadowSimulator.simulate_session`:
+  - Derives a shadow backend based on influence readiness and routing candidates.
+  - Compares shadow vs actual routing outcomes.
+  - Computes an estimated risk.
+
+10.4.2. Inputs
+- Event log for a session (routing and failure events).
+- `InfluenceReadinessRecord`.
+- Hint impact reports (optional).
+
+10.4.3. Effect on Execution
+- Observational-only; results are used to compute risk levels.
+- No code writes these results into Router configuration directly.
+
+10.5. Approval
+
+10.5.1. What It Computes
+- `knez/cognitive/approval/api.ApprovalService`:
+  - Evaluates shadow influence summaries against policy rules.
+  - Produces an `ApprovalRecord` indicating approved/rejected state.
+
+10.5.2. Inputs
+- `InfluenceReadinessRecord`.
+- `ShadowInfluenceSummary`.
+- Policy rules in `PolicyEngine`.
+
+10.5.3. Effect on Execution
+- Records approval decisions in `ApprovalAuditLog`.
+- Influence application still requires runtime switches and adapter logic; no automated mutation of Router state is performed.
+
+11. TAQWIN INTEGRATION (REAL BEHAVIOR)
+
+11.1. TAQWIN â†’ KNEZ Requests
+
+11.1.1. call_chat_completions
+- `taqwin/knez_client.py` `call_chat_completions`:
+  - Builds payload with:
+    - `model`, `messages`, `stream=False`, `session_id`.
+  - Sends POST to `KNEZ_BASE_URL/v1/chat/completions`.
+  - Raises on non-2xx HTTP status.
+
+11.1.2. send_taqwin_response
+- Sends POST to `KNEZ_BASE_URL/taqwin/events` with TAQWIN-produced payload.
+
+11.2. KNEZ TAQWIN Endpoint Validation
+
+11.2.1. TaqwinValidator
+- `knez/integrations/taqwin/validator.py`:
+  - Parses and validates payloads using `schemas.py`.
+  - Verifies that the session exists by consulting `EventStore`.
+  - If session is unknown:
+    - Marks payload as invalid.
+    - Emits `taqwin_payload_rejected` event with `EventType.REFLECTION`.
+
+11.2.2. Adapter Behavior
+- `knez/integrations/taqwin/adapter.taqwin_events`:
+  - Returns `{"status": "rejected"}` for invalid or unknown sessions.
+  - Emits:
+    - `taqwin_input_received`.
+    - `taqwin_analysis_completed`.
+    - `taqwin_proposal_observed` for each proposal.
+  - Returns `{"status": "accepted"}` for valid payloads.
+
+11.3. Limitations
+
+11.3.1. No Direct Influence on Router from TAQWIN
+- TAQWIN events are ingested as part of the event stream and can be used by cognitive components.
+- There is no direct path that uses TAQWIN proposals to modify routing decisions in real time.
+
+12. IDE / COMPATIBILITY LAYER STATUS
+
+12.1. What knez/compat Adds
+
+12.1.1. Endpoints
+- `POST /v1/chat/completions`: OpenAI-style completions.
+- `POST /v1/responses`: OpenAI Responses API.
+- `GET /v1/models`: model listing with capability metadata.
+
+12.1.2. Behavior vs Core
+- All business logic (routing, memory, failover, sessions) stays in core KNEZ (`knez_core`).
+- Compat layer is a pure translation/proxy layer over HTTP+in-process FastAPI.
+
+12.2. How It Proxies
+
+12.2.1. HTTP Proxy
+- Uses `httpx.AsyncClient(app=core_app, base_url="http://core")` to simulate HTTP calls to KNEZ core.
+- Forwards headers and JSON body.
+
+12.3. SSE Normalization
+
+12.3.1. Standardization
+- `_normalize_sse_stream` ensures SSE output complies with:
+  - `data: <json>\n\n` frames for chunks.
+  - `data: [DONE]\n\n` end-of-stream marker.
+  - Optional suppression of keep-alive frames based on `KNEZ_SSE_KEEPALIVE`.
+
+12.4. Responses API Mapping
+
+12.4.1. Mapping Logic
+- `compat_responses` maps:
+  - `input` or `messages` to core `messages`.
+  - Always uses non-streaming core path.
+  - Extracts final text and wraps it in a Responses-style `response` object.
+
+12.5. Capability Flags
+
+12.5.1. feature_flags
+- `CompatFeatureFlags` with fields:
+  - `supports_tools: bool = False`.
+  - `supports_streaming: bool = True`.
+  - `supports_inline_completion: bool = False`.
+  - `supports_responses: bool = True`.
+
+12.5.2. /v1/models Exposure
+- `GET /v1/models` attaches these flags under `metadata`.
