+15. LIMITATIONS & FAILURE MODES
+
+15.1. Identified Limitations (Code-Provable)
+- No authentication or authorization: all HTTP endpoints are open.
+- No built-in rate limiting.
+- No direct configuration exposure for toggling cognitive features via HTTP.
+- No persistence of final router/influence configuration beyond process memory.
+
+15.2. Failure Modes
+- EventStore overflow:
+  - Uses a bounded queue; when full, events may be dropped (`_dropped` counter).
+- Redis outages:
+  - Checkpointing reads and writes may fail; tests and code indicate metrics and pressure counters, but no external alerting is implemented in this codebase.
+- SQLite errors:
+  - If SQLite files cannot be written (permissions, disk full), sessions, snapshots, or memory cannot be persisted; error handling is limited to exceptions being raised, not always converted into user-visible responses.
+
